  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Users with the Manager role and higher can view the Profitability reports to see margins for sales based on catalog Item Type.</p><h3 id=\"Reports:CheckYourGrossProfitMarginsbyItemType-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1937866763/Reporting+Resources+with+Video\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1937866763\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Reporting Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934360593/Reports+Real-time+Profitability\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934360593\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Reports: Real-time Profitability</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934524447/Maintaining+an+Accurate+Profitability+Report\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934524447\" data-linked-resource-version=\"3\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Maintaining an Accurate Profitability Report</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934393345/Reports+Check+Your+Gross+Profit+Margins+by+Item+Type\">Reports: Check Your Gross Profit Margins by Item Type</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933738176/Calculating+Overhead+Rate\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933738176\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Calculating Overhead Rate</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934360642/RepairQ+Accounting+Principles\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934360642\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RepairQ Accounting Principles</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934393345/image-20230627-152834.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h2 id=\"Reports:CheckYourGrossProfitMarginsbyItemType-ViewingtheProfitabilitybyTypeReport\">Viewing the Profitability by Type Report</h2><p /><p>1. On the Navigation Bar, click <strong>Reports</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934393345/image-20230627-152837.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>2. On the Reports page, click on the <strong>Sales dropdown</strong>\u00a0along the top row of report categories. From the available list, click <strong>Profitability by Type</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934393345/image-20230627-152840.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>3. Use the available filters to scope results based on the assigned parameters.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934393345/image-20230627-152842.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><ul><li><p><strong>Date Range</strong> - Select a date range for your scope of results.</p></li><li><p><strong>Location</strong> - Select a specific location or run an aggregate report for multiple stores.</p></li><li><p><strong>Ticket Status</strong> - By default, reporting will focus on Closed tickets. You can select to focus on Closed tickets, Open tickets, or All tickets.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Note</strong>: Open tickets are considered projected totals, per <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934360642/RepairQ+Accounting+Principles\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934360642\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RepairQ Accounting Principles</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>and are not considered as revenue.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Warranty Providers</strong> - Filter by specific warranty providers, or include all.</p></li><li><p><strong>Include Labor Costs</strong> - Labor is added by hours entered on ticket items and the staff member's pay rate found in their <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1929379890/Staff+Management+Add+and+Deactivate+Staff+Profiles\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1929379890\" data-linked-resource-version=\"27\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Staff User Profile</a>.</p></li></ul><p /><p>4. Once you have set your filters, click <strong>Apply Filters</strong> to run the report.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934393345/image-20230627-152845.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: You can click <strong>Hide/Show Filters</strong> on the upper-right side of the page to collapse/expand the filters when viewing reports. You can also click <strong>Sales By Catalog Item</strong> to view the Sales by Catalog Item Report to view a sales breakdown of catalog items sorted by their Item Type.\u00a0</p><p /><h2 id=\"Reports:CheckYourGrossProfitMarginsbyItemType-ProfitabilitybyItemType\">Profitability by Item Type</h2><p>The Profitability by Item Type report will show a summarized breakdown for each item type with details for the following:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Gross Sales</strong> - A sum of ticket item subtotals and excludes any restock fees, discounts, returns, and taxes applied.</p></li><li><p><strong>Gross Returns\u00a0</strong>- A sum of returns on\u00a0</p></li><li><p><strong>Restock Fees</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Net Discounts</strong> - A total of any discounts applied to the sale minus returns discounts.</p></li><li><p><strong>Net Sales</strong> - A total of gross sales with subtracted net discounts and gross returns.</p></li><li><p><strong>COGS</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Gross Profit\u00a0</strong>- A total of net sales with subtracted COGS amount.</p></li><li><p><strong>GPM% (Gross Profit Margin Percentage) </strong>-\u00a0 The total of (net sales minus COGS) divided by net sales.</p></li></ul><p>\u00a0Totals for all columns can be found at the bottom row of the report.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934393345/image-20230627-152849.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
